{
  "article_id": "Stuart1879_Jan28",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "I well recollect with what boyish pleasure and absorbing interest I followed Robinson Crusoe in his lonely travels and daily occupations on the",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "island of Juan Fernandez",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_jf",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", little thinking that in later years I would find a similar case on",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "this far-off coast",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_socalcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "; but such is the fact, and my narrative is not only based upon facts, but is fact, the knowledge of the circumstances having been obtained from",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the discoverers",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "cdi",
          "col",
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ",",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "captors",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "cdi",
          "col",
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the physician",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "bri",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "who attended during the last sickness of",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "my feminine \"Crusoe,\"",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "the",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "heroine of San Nicolas Island",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Having heard that"
      },
      {
        "text": "an Indian woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "had lived a lonely life of eighteen years—from 1835 to 1853—on"
      },
      {
        "text": "one of the many islands off this coast",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", I was anxious to learn more about it than the varying and contradictory reports in general circulation gave me, but was not able to do so until a short time ago, when, through an interpreter, I consulted"
      },
      {
        "text": "Messrs. George Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and"
      },
      {
        "text": "Charles Brown",
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", two of"
      },
      {
        "text": "the party",
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "cdi",
          "col",
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "who brought her from"
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "to"
      },
      {
        "text": "this place",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and"
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Nidever",
        "entity_key": "sni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who had charge of her after she landed."
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Nidever",
        "entity_key": "sni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was consulted through an interpreter conversant with the Spanish language."
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "is well advanced in years, about eighty, but retains his faculties to a good degree. A frontiersman from early life, he spent many years as trapper and huntsman among the Indians of the northwest previous to coming here in 1835. He became expert in the use of the rifle, and maintains his reputation even to the present day. Without the aid of glasses he can put a pistol ball into the head of a gopher at twenty five feet. Although an American by birth he now converses entirely in the Spanish language. [Not \"entirely.\"—ED]"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Mr. Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "said: \"My occupation has been that of otter hunting. When I came here, in 1835 I found two other Americans,"
      },
      {
        "text": "Isaac J. Sparks",
        "entity_key": "isp",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and"
      },
      {
        "text": "Lewis T. Burton",
        "entity_key": "lbu",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", engaged in the same business. They chartered"
      },
      {
        "text": "a schooner",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "of twenty tons burden, built at"
      },
      {
        "text": "Monterey",
        "entity_key": "ci_mo",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", called"
      },
      {
        "text": "Peor es Nada",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "("
      },
      {
        "text": "Better than Nothing",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ",) for a trip to the coast of"
      },
      {
        "text": "Lower California",
        "entity_key": "re_baja",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", on an otter expedition, leaving"
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "about the first of May, 1835. I did not accompany the expedition. Not being as successful as those in charge expected, three months later the"
      },
      {
        "text": "Peor es Nada",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "put into"
      },
      {
        "text": "San Pedro",
        "entity_key": "ci_sp",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", the port or landing of"
      },
      {
        "text": "Los Angeles",
        "entity_key": "ci_la",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", on her return trip[.] From"
      },
      {
        "text": "San Pedro",
        "entity_key": "ci_sp",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "she went to the"
      },
      {
        "text": "Island of San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", about seventy miles southwest from"
      },
      {
        "text": "San Pedro",
        "entity_key": "ci_sp",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and a little further southeast from"
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "for the purpose of removing"
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians then on the island",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "to"
      },
      {
        "text": "the main land",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and returned with"
      },
      {
        "text": "eighteen men, women and children",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "as told me by"
      },
      {
        "text": "Isaac J. Sparks",
        "entity_key": "isp",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "[.] How long"
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "had been residents of"
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", how they got there, and by whose authority they were removed, I know not."
      },
      {
        "text": "One of the Indians",
        "entity_key": "bha",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", rather dwarfed in intellect, but possessing the physical strength three or four ordinary men, remained at"
      },
      {
        "text": "San Pedro",
        "entity_key": "ci_sp",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "[;]"
      },
      {
        "text": "two of the women",
        "entity_keys": [
          "Nicolenowoman1",
          "Nicolenowoman2"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "were taken as concubines by"
      },
      {
        "text": "two Americans",
        "entity_keys": [
          "laresident1",
          "laresident2"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "living in"
      },
      {
        "text": "Los Angeles County",
        "entity_key": "co_la",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ";"
      },
      {
        "text": "the balance of the party",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "divided, part going to"
      },
      {
        "text": "Los Angeles",
        "entity_key": "mi_losangeles",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "and part to"
      },
      {
        "text": "San Gabriel Mission",
        "entity_key": "mi_sg",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      },
      {
        "text": "Those two men",
        "entity_keys": [
          "laresident1",
          "laresident2"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "who selected"
      },
      {
        "text": "their concubines",
        "entity_keys": [
          "Nicolenowoman1",
          "Nicolenowoman2"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "from"
      },
      {
        "text": "the party",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "took an active part in having"
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "removed.\""
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "According to the information I have obtained from"
      },
      {
        "text": "the three persons consulted",
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "cdi",
          "sni"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "through the interpreter, the history of"
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indian woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ","
      },
      {
        "text": "the feminine Crusoe",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", is as follows[:]"
      },
      {
        "text": "She was absent gathering wood when",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the others",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "were taken away but returned to the camp or quarters and finding them deserted, followed in time to be taken aboard",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the schooner",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ", but not finding",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her children",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "there, one",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a babe at the breast",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the other",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "about three years old, she plunged into the water and swam ashore in search of them.",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Unable to find"
      },
      {
        "text": "her children",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", she returned to the beach just in time to see"
      },
      {
        "text": "the schooner",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "leaving. She called to"
      },
      {
        "text": "those on board",
        "entity_keys": [
          "bhagroup",
          "1835crew",
          "chu",
          "isp",
          "iwi",
          "jsjo",
          "jdy",
          "lbu",
          "natam_hawaiian",
          "nativeamericans"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", but the only reply she got and which she remembered to the day of her death, was \"mañana,\" pronounced mah-nyah-nah, the Spanish word for \"to-morrow,\" evidently meaning that"
      },
      {
        "text": "the schooner",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "would return for her to-morrow or the following day. She threw herself down on the beach and cried long and bitterly. She did not find"
      },
      {
        "text": "her children",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and supposed they were either taken off by"
      },
      {
        "text": "the schooner",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "or carried away and devoured by the wild dogs on"
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". She became very sick and lay a long time without either water or food, but finally recovered and forgot her grief in wandering about"
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". She lived on a plant resembling the cabbage, called by Californians \"palosanto,\" and a root known by the name of \"corcomite;\" also a yellow root, the name of which was not given, and seal or sea-lion blubber. As she had abalone-shell fish hooks and lines made of the sinews of the seal, it is probable she supplied herself with fish from the ocean."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "An approaching storm and night coming on, the water being quite shoal about"
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and unsafe for a vessel during a high wind, they were compelled to leave for the safety of"
      },
      {
        "text": "the schooner",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ", intending to return at a future time for"
      },
      {
        "text": "the deserted woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      },
      {
        "text": "The vessel",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "ran before the gale and reached"
      },
      {
        "text": "San Pedro",
        "entity_key": "ci_sp",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "harbor in safety;"
      },
      {
        "text": "but circumstances did not permit a return prior to the loss of",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the schooner",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "in a storm a few weeks later, and the distance to",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "was too great to be safely made in the small shore boats.",
        "tropes": [
          12
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "In 1851",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. Nidever",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "visited",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "otter hunting, and saw signs of a human inhabitant. He saw a footprint made during the previous rainy season, sunken deeply in the now dry, hard ground, and from the size judged it to be that of a woman. Also, three small circular enclosures about two hundred yards from the beach and about a mile apart. They were about six feet in diameter, made of brush, the walls five feet high, with a small opening on one side. Near these openings were sticks of drift-wood stuck in the ground in the form of a tripod, supporting dried seal blubber. These enclosures appeared to be simply wind breaks, affording no protection from the rain. The investigation was pursued no further, as an approaching storm compelled them to leave",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. Nidever",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "having seen many otters on his first trip to",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "made a second during the Winter of 1852, and being requested by",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Mission Fathers",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "jru",
          "aji",
          "sanchez",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "of",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "mi_santabarbaramission",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", had determined to make a careful hunt for",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the supposed lone inhabitant of the island",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". The head of",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "being better supplied with fresh water, closer to the beachand better facilities for fishing, and the altitude such as to command a view of the greater portion of",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "coast",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_calcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "he supposed if alive she would be found there, and made his arrangements accordingly.",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "He and his party",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "tje",
          "nativeamericans"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "found the same, or similar enclosures, above mentioned, and the tripod sticks supporting renewed pieces of blubber. In the neighborhood of the huts or wind breaks, were seven or eight wild dogs about the size of a cayote, (a small wolf on this coast), and in color black and white.",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. N.",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "said he had seen the same kind of dogs among the Northwest Indians. They appeared to be very wild. Within half a mile of the head of",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "they discovered a basket in the crotch of a bush or small tree, covered with a seal skin, and containing a dress made of shag's skins (the shag is a species of duck on",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "this coast",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_calcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
